# Testing Patterns

## Stack

- **Jest** with `ts-jest/presets/js-with-ts-esm` (ESM mode)
- **jsdom** environment
- **@testing-library/react** + **@testing-library/jest-dom**
- CSS Modules → `identity-obj-proxy`

## Test File Locations

Tests live alongside source in `packages/core/`:

```
packages/core/
├── lib/__tests__/
├── lib/data/__tests__/
├── reducer/actions/__tests__/
├── store/slices/__tests__/
├── types/__tests__/
└── components/Puck/__tests__/
```

Naming: `*.spec.ts` or `*.spec.tsx`. One exception: `components/Puck/__tests__/index.tsx`.

## Running Tests

- From root: `yarn test` (Turbo delegates to `packages/core`)
- From core: `cd packages/core && yarn test`
- Single file: `cd packages/core && yarn jest path/to/file.spec.ts`

## Conventions

- Tests are appreciated but not strictly required for every PR
- Complex code or public API changes should include tests
- The test suite currently covers only `packages/core`
- Plugins and field packages do not have test suites yet

## Configuration

Jest config: `packages/core/jest.config.ts`
- `useESM: true` in ts-jest config
- `transformIgnorePatterns` allows `@preact/signals-core`, `@preact/signals-react`, and `@dnd-kit` through
- `moduleNameMapper` maps `*.module.css` to `identity-obj-proxy`
